text.section:
A person who applies for a license as a resident insurance producer shall:
in the case of an applicant who is an individual, submit to the Commissioner a uniform application and declare under penalty of refusal, suspension, or revocation of the license that the statements made in the uniform application are true, correct, and complete to the best of the individual's knowledge and belief;
in the case of an applicant that is a business entity, submit to the Commissioner a uniform business entity application;
pay the applicable fee required by § 2-112 of this article for a license;
file on the form and in the manner that the Commissioner provides:
any trade name to be used by the applicant;
the business address of the applicant; and
the name and residence address of each individual who holds a license and does business under the trade name; and
submit to the Commissioner any additional information or documentation that the Commissioner requires, including any information or documentation to determine the professional competence, good character, and trustworthiness of the applicant.
